actorDefinition.readme:
# ‚ú®Leads Finder ‚Äî Effortless Data Extraction

*A cost-effective alternative to ZoomInfo, Lusha & Apollo. Get verified B2B emails, LinkedIn profiles, and rich firmographics at scale.*

---

## üöÄ What this actor does

Leads Finder generates **targeted B2B contact lists** using advanced filters (job title, **Location/City**, industry, tech stack, revenue, funding, etc.) and returns **verified emails**, LinkedIn URLs, and detailed **company data** ‚Äî ready for CRM or outreach.
**Free plan note:** Users on the free Apify plan can fetch up to **100 leads/run**.

**Support:** [codecrafter70@gmail.com](mailto:codecrafter70@gmail.com)

---

## üß≠ Quick start (UI)

1. Open the actor, set **üìÅ File name / Run label** (optional).
2. Choose your filters (e.g., **üëî Job Title** = "Marketing Manager", **üåç Location** = "United States", **üè≠ Industry** = "SaaS").
3. Set **#Ô∏è‚É£ Number of leads to fetch** (default 50,000; leave empty to fetch all that match).
4. Click **Run**. When finished, download results from the **Dataset** tab or use the **Overview** table.

> **Location vs City:** Use **Location** for a *region/country/state*. To target a single city, **leave Location empty** and use **City** only. (Same logic for the Exclude fields.)

---

## üß© Input schema (fields you can use)

> Fields accept arrays unless noted.

### General

* **fetch_count** *(integer, default 50000)* ‚Äî Max leads to fetch. Leave empty to fetch all matches.
* **file_name** *(string)* ‚Äî Custom run label / export name.

### People targeting

* **contact_job_title** / **contact_not_job_title** ‚Äî Include/Exclude titles ("realtor", "software developer", "teacher", ‚Ä¶).
* **seniority_level** ‚Äî Founder, Owner, C-Level, Director, VP, Head, Manager, Senior, Entry, Trainee.
* **functional_level** ‚Äî C-Level, Finance, Product, Engineering, Design, HR, IT, Legal, Marketing, Operations, Sales, Support.

### Location (Include)

* **contact_location** ‚Äî Region/Country/State (e.g., *EMEA*, *United States*, *California, US*).
* **contact_city** ‚Äî One or more cities (use this **instead of** Location when you want city-level targeting only).

### Location (Exclude)

* **contact_not_location** ‚Äî Region/Country/State to exclude.
* **contact_not_city** ‚Äî One or more cities to exclude.

### Email quality

* **email_status** ‚Äî `validated`, `not_validated`, `unknown` *(prefill: validated)*

### Company targeting

* **company_domain** ‚Äî Limit to specific domains (e.g., `google.com`, `https://apple.com`).
* **size** ‚Äî 0‚Äì1, 2‚Äì10, 11‚Äì20, 21‚Äì50, 51‚Äì100, 101‚Äì200, 201‚Äì500, 501‚Äì1000, 1001‚Äì2000, 2001‚Äì5000, 10000+
* **company_industry** / **company_not_industry** ‚Äî Include/Exclude industries.
* **company_keywords** / **company_not_keywords** ‚Äî Include/Exclude free-text keywords.
* **min_revenue**, **max_revenue** ‚Äî Revenue bands (100K ‚Üí 10B).
* **funding** ‚Äî Seed, Angel, Series A‚Ä¶F, Venture, Debt, Convertible, PE, Other.

---

## üì§ Output schema (what you get)

Results are written to the run's **Dataset** and rendered in the **Overview** table with these columns:

**Person**

* `first_name`, `last_name`, `full_name`, `job_title`, `headline`, `functional_level`, `seniority_level`
* `email` *(verified when available)*
* `linkedin` *(profile link)*
* `city`, `state`, `country`

**Company**

* `company_name`, `company_domain`, `company_website` *(link)*, `company_linkedin` *(link)*, `company_linkedin_uid`
* `company_size`, `industry`, `company_description`
* `company_annual_revenue`, `company_annual_revenue_clean`
* `company_total_funding`, `company_total_funding_clean`
* `company_founded_year`, `company_phone`
* `company_street_address`, `company_city`, `company_state`, `company_country`, `company_postal_code`, `company_full_address`
* `company_market_cap` *(if public)*

**Context**

* `keywords`, `company_technologies`

---

## üîé Examples

### Example 1 ‚Äî US SaaS marketing leaders

* **contact_job_title:** `["Head of Marketing","VP Marketing","CMO"]`
* **functional_level:** `["marketing"]`
* **contact_location:** `["united states"]`
* **company_industry:** `["computer software","internet","information technology & services","marketing & advertising","saas"]`
* **email_status:** `["validated"]`
* **fetch_count:** `5000`

### Example 2 ‚Äî UK CTOs

* **contact_job_title:** `["CTO","Head of Engineering","VP Engineering"]`
* **contact_location:** `["united kingdom"]`
* **email_status:** `["validated","unknown"]`

### Example 3 ‚Äî Amsterdam city-only (no broader Location)

* **contact_city:** `["amsterdam"]`
* **contact_location:** *(leave empty)*

---

## ‚úÖ Best practices

* **Location vs City:** Choose **one**. Use *Location* for region/country/state **or** leave it empty and use *City* for city-only targeting. Same rule for Exclude.
* **Start broad, then narrow.** Begin with Location + title, then add industry/revenue/funding.
* **Use include & exclude.** Quickly remove irrelevant sectors with `company_not_industry` / `company_not_keywords`.
* **Prefer validated emails.** Keep `email_status = ["validated"]` for outreach-ready lists; add `unknown` to increase volume.
* **Deduplicate downstream.** If you merge runs, dedupe by `email` ‚Üí `linkedin` ‚Üí (`full_name`,`company_domain`).
* **Stay compliant.** Use for B2B prospecting; follow GDPR/CCPA/PECR and local rules.

---

## üß™ Output view (in the Apify UI)

The **Overview** tab shows a sortable table with links for `company_website`, `linkedin`, and `company_linkedin`. Export any time to CSV/JSON/XLSX from the Dataset.

---

## üß∞ API usage

Run via API with the same input JSON as the UI.

1. POST a run with your input JSON.
2. Poll for completion.
3. Fetch dataset items (JSON/CSV).

*(See Apify docs for `runs`, `datasets` endpoints.)*

---

## üíµ Pricing & limits

* **From $1.5 / 1,000 leads** (cheaper than typical ZoomInfo/Lusha/Apollo seat pricing).
* On the **free Apify plan**, the platform caps at **100 leads/run**.

---

## üßØ Troubleshooting

* **Few or zero results?** Loosen filters (remove `company_not_*`, broaden Location, allow `unknown` email status). Try title synonyms ("Demand Gen" vs "Growth Marketing").
* **Too many results?** Add industry, revenue, funding, or switch from region to country/state/city.
* **Geography mismatches?** Don't mix broad regions with countries/states/cities; use *either* Location *or* City for the same target.

---

## ‚ú® Changelog (high level)

* v1.1 ‚Äî **Simplified location filters**: replaced Region/Country/State trio with **Location (Region/Country/State)** + **City**; mirrored for Exclude.
* v1.0 ‚Äî Initial release with People/Company/Tech/Revenue/Funding filters, validated email preference, and LinkedIn enrichment.

# ‚ú®Leads Finder ‚Äî Effortless Data Extraction

*A cost-effective alternative to ZoomInfo, Lusha & Apollo. Get verified B2B emails, LinkedIn profiles, and rich firmographics at scale.*

---

## üöÄ What this actor does

Leads Finder generates **targeted B2B contact lists** using advanced filters (job title, **Location/City**, industry, tech stack, revenue, funding, etc.) and returns **verified emails**, LinkedIn URLs, and detailed **company data** ‚Äî ready for CRM or outreach.
**Free plan note:** Users on the free Apify plan can fetch up to **100 leads/run**.

**Support:** [codecrafter70@gmail.com](mailto:codecrafter70@gmail.com)

---

## üß≠ Quick start (UI)

1. Open the actor, set **üìÅ File name / Run label** (optional).
2. Choose your filters (e.g., **üëî Job Title** = "Marketing Manager", **üåç Location** = "United States", **üè≠ Industry** = "SaaS").
3. Set **#Ô∏è‚É£ Number of leads to fetch** (default 50,000; leave empty to fetch all that match).
4. Click **Run**. When finished, download results from the **Dataset** tab or use the **Overview** table.

> **Location vs City:** Use **Location** for a *region/country/state*. To target a single city, **leave Location empty** and use **City** only. (Same logic for the Exclude fields.)

---

## üß© Input schema (fields you can use)

> Fields accept arrays unless noted.

### General

## ‚úÖ Best practices

* **Location vs City:** Choose **one**. Use *Location* for region/country/state **or** leave it empty and use *City* for city-only targeting. Same rule for Exclude.
* **Start broad, then narrow.** Begin with Location + title, then add industry/revenue/funding.
* **Use include & exclude.** Quickly remove irrelevant sectors with `company_not_industry` / `company_not_keywords`.
* **Prefer validated emails.** Keep `email_status = ["validated"]` for outreach-ready lists; add `unknown` to increase volume.
* **Deduplicate downstream.** If you merge runs, dedupe by `email` ‚Üí `linkedin` ‚Üí (`full_name`,`company_domain`).
* **Stay compliant.** Use for B2B prospecting; follow GDPR/CCPA/PECR and local rules.

## üßØ Troubleshooting

* **Few or zero results?** Loosen filters (remove `company_not_*`, broaden Location, allow `unknown` email status). Try title synonyms ("Demand Gen" vs "Growth Marketing").
* **Too many results?** Add industry, revenue, funding, or switch from region to country/state/city.
* **Geography mismatches?** Don't mix broad regions with countries/states/cities; use *either* Location *or* City for the same target.
